        "last_activity_date": 1386578713,
        "creation_date": 1386314925,
        "answer_count": 3,
        "title": "How to get string from a parse in java instead of getting id?",
        "body": "<p>I am making an android app and currently stuck on signup page.\nTrying to enter values in database using parse and storing the database on parse.com\n The values are entered in <code>EditText<\/code> box and are having some id say <code>\"name\"<\/code>\n On using that for database, my java file includes command like<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> parseObject text=new parseObject(\"Signup\");\n\n text.put(\"Key_id_name\", R.id.name);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>//Due to this, id of EditText box is coming in database.<\/p>\n\n<p>Kindly help me how to get the value entered in that.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 20418434,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android",
            "xml-parsing",
            "parse-platform",
            "developer-tools"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "is_answered": false,
        "view_count": 484,
        "last_edit_date": 1386374689
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/KPrYF.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1057674,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1060037,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1060037/jayamohan",
                "reputation": 12975,
                "display_name": "Jayamohan"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386578713,
            "creation_date": 1386315132,
            "body": "<p>Use <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/EditText.html#getText%28%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">getText()<\/a> method of <code>EditText<\/code> class as below.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>EditText field = (EditText) findViewById(R.id.name);\nString fieldValue = field.getText().toString();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Then add it to your map<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>text.put(\"Key_id_name\", fieldValue);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><em>R.id.name<\/em> will simply give you the generated Id and not the value.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418483,
            "question_id": 20418434,
            "last_edit_date": 1386578713
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/15438ef634ef9d77e358a2e3743d05ff?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 438686,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 827110,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/827110/amulya-khare",
                "reputation": 7708,
                "display_name": "Amulya Khare"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386315180,
            "creation_date": 1386315180,
            "body": "<p>You should do something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>TextView view = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.name);\nparseObject text=new parseObject(\"Signup\");\ntext.put(\"Key_id_name\", view.getText().toString());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418498,
            "question_id": 20418434
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7facb7c96c0befd657353ca27dcd1d42?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 431745,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 816017,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/816017/erik-%c5%bdivkovi%c4%87",
                "reputation": 5535,
                "display_name": "Erik Živković",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386315318,
            "creation_date": 1386315318,
            "body": "<p>I guess your view has a TextView with the id R.id.name?<\/p>\n\n<p>In that case you should use findViewById(R.id.name) in your activity code <\/p>\n\n<p>See these docs:\n<a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Activity.html#findViewById(int)\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Activity.html#findViewById(int)<\/a>\n<a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/TextView.html#getText()\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/TextView.html#getText()<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>TextView idText = (TextView) findViewById(R.id.name);\nString idString = idText.getText().toString();\ntext.put(\"Key_id_name\", idString);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Good luck =)<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20418531,
            "question_id": 20418434
        }
    ],
